What is the difference between @PathVariable and @RequestParam ?

1. @PathVariable (Resource Identity)
This extracts values directly from the URI path itself.

URL Look: http://localhost:8080/orders/1
Mapping: @GetMapping("/orders/{id}")
When to use: Use this when you are specifically identifying a single, unique resource (like fetching Order ID 1). It is the core of RESTful design syntax.

2. @RequestParam (Filtering & Modifiers)
This extracts values from the Query String (everything that comes after the ? in a URL).

URL Look: http://localhost:8080/orders?month=2023-10&sort=desc
Mapping: @GetMapping("/orders")
When to use: Use this when you are filtering a collection of resources, sorting, paginating, or providing optional flags. In our case, extracting the month to filter down the entire database of orders!
In Summary: Use @PathVariable to answer "Which exact item?", and use @RequestParam to answer "How do you want this list filtered?".

